At the moment, No Priority is indexed as - 1.
When this sorts, it retreives the Priority GenericValue from the ConstantsManager to sort on.
As there is no GenericValue for "-1" it returns null.

The problem with this is that the code below assumes that a null alue should be placed before an non null value.  For priorities this is not the case, the null value should be the last.

{code:title=JiraLuceneFieldCache.java|borderStyle=solid}
public Object[] getCustom(IndexReader reader, String field, MappedSortComparator comparator)  throws IOException
{
....
                            Object currentValue = retArray[termDocs.doc()];
                            //only replace the value if it is earlier than the current value
                            if (currentValue == null || comparator.getComparator().compare(termval, currentValue) < 1)
                                retArray[termDocs.doc()] = termval;

...
}
{code} 

You can remove the null check and let each comparator deal with null values but the above code needs to take this into account as the null check is done for not yet set rather than null objects.

The code should deal with null objects and delegate the camparison of null objects to the individual comparators and let the decide how the null should be handled.
All the individual comparators need to be changed to deal with null values. E.g. SequencedGVsComparator.java

